----
There&#39;s a framework [Reflections][1] you can use it to do it very easily:
```java
public static void main(String... args) {
    Set&lt;Class&lt;? extends FooChild&gt;&gt; classes = findAllClasses(&quot;foo&quot;, FooChild.class);

    for (Class&lt;?&gt; cls : classes) {
        // do smth
    }
}

public static &lt;T&gt; Set&lt;Class&lt;? extends T&gt;&gt; findAllClasses(String packageName, Class&lt;T&gt; cls) {
    return new Reflections(packageName).getSubTypesOf(cls);
}
```

  [1]: https://github.com/ronmamo/reflections

