In case you check the implemenation, you will see:
```java
public static int compare(int x, int y) {
    return (x &lt; y) ? -1 : ((x == y) ? 0 : 1);
}
```
But in java doc of this method it says, that:
```
@return the value {@code 0} if {@code x == y};
        a value less than {@code 0} if {@code x &lt; y}; and
        a value greater than {@code 0} if {@code x &gt; y}
```

You definitely can check for `-1,0,1`, but I recommend you to check `&lt;0,0,&gt;0` - this is **much more reliable**. Just to protect the code.

```java
if(Integer.compare(2,1) == 1) {} // this is 100% correct
if(Integer.compare(2,1) &gt; 0)  {} // this is 999% correct
```

